[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] UEFI executes independent programs known as UEFI applications, which are stored as files on the EFI system partition.
[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] These can be launched via the UEFI Shell, the firmware boot manager, or other UEFI applications, and may be developed independently of the original equipment manufacturer (OEM).
[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] A type of UEFI application is an OS boot loader such as GRUB, rEFInd, systemd-boot, and Windows Boot Manager, which loads some OS files into memory and executes them.
