[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] It is also common for a boot manager to have a textual user interface to allow the user to select the desired OS (or setup utility) from a list of available boot options.
[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] On PC platforms, firmware supporting UEFI boot is often referred to as a "UEFI BIOS", though some newer x86 platforms exclude CSM support entirely.
