[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] In this scenario, booting is performed in the same way as on legacy BIOS-based systems, by ignoring the partition table and relying on the content of a boot sector.
[src:secure-boot-measured/unified-extensible-firmware-interface] The Compatibility Support Module allows legacy operating systems and some legacy option ROMs that do not support UEFI to still be used.
